              "note": "use $\\sin^2\\theta + \\cos^2\\theta = 1$ or a 3-4-5 triangle"
            },
            {
              "mark": "A1",
              "note": "$\\cos^2\\theta = 1 - \\tfrac{9}{25} = \\tfrac{16}{25}$"
            },
            {
              "mark": "A1",
              "note": "$\\cos\\theta = \\dfrac{4}{5}$ (positive, $\\theta$ acute)"
            }
          ],
          "answer": "$\\cos\\theta = \\dfrac{4}{5}$",
          "solution": "**Plan:** use the Pythagorean identity.$$\\cos^2\\theta = 1 - \\sin^2\\theta = 1 - \\tfrac{9}{25} = \\tfrac{16}{25}$$Since $\\theta$ is acute, $\\cos\\theta > 0$, so $\\cos\\theta = \\tfrac{4}{5}$.",
          "verify": [
            "Eq(sqrt(1 - Rational(3,5)**2), Rational(4,5))"
          ]
        },
        {
          "label": "b",
          "body": "Hence find the exact value of $\\sin 2\\theta$.",
          "marks": 3,
          "markscheme": [
            {
              "mark": "M1",
              "note": "use $\\sin 2\\theta = 2\\sin\\theta\\cos\\theta$"
            },
            {
              "mark": "A1",
              "note": "$2 \\cdot \\tfrac{3}{5} \\cdot \\tfrac{4}{5}$"
            },
            {
              "mark": "A1",
              "note": "$\\sin 2\\theta = \\dfrac{24}{25}$"
            }
          ],
          "answer": "$\\sin 2\\theta = \\dfrac{24}{25}$",
          "solution": "Use the double-angle identity with the values above:$$\\sin 2\\theta = 2\\sin\\theta\\cos\\theta = 2 \\cdot \\tfrac{3}{5} \\cdot \\tfrac{4}{5} = \\tfrac{24}{25}$$",
          "verify": [
            "Eq(2*Rational(3,5)*Rational(4,5), Rational(24,25))"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "contextIntro": "The angle $\\theta$ is acute and $\\sin\\theta = \\dfrac{3}{5}$."
    },
    {
