          ],
          "answer": "$(1, 0)$ and $(5, 0)$",
          "solution": "**Plan:** the $x$-intercepts occur where $f(x) = 0$.$$x^2 - 6x + 5 = (x - 1)(x - 5) = 0$$So $x = 1$ or $x = 5$; the graph crosses at $(1, 0)$ and $(5, 0)$.",
