              "mark": "M1",
              "note": "complete the square: half of $-6$ is $-3$"
            },
            {
              "mark": "A1",
              "note": "$f(x) = (x - 3)^2 - 4$"
            },
            {
              "mark": "A1",
              "note": "minimum value $-4$ (at $x = 3$)"
            }
          ],
          "answer": "$f(x) = (x - 3)^2 - 4$; minimum value $-4$",
          "solution": "Complete the square:$$f(x) = (x^2 - 6x + 9) - 9 + 5 = (x - 3)^2 - 4$$The square is never negative, so the least value is $-4$, attained at $x = 3$.",
          "verify": [
            "Eq(expand((x - 3)**2 - 4), x**2 - 6*x + 5)"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "contextIntro": "The function $f$ is given by $f(x) = x^2 - 6x + 5$."
    },
